@Michael Keaton I recently listened to a released recording of one of your arguments. I won’t put in my two cents on her again. My thoughts very much stand where that is concerned. If anything the recording solidified my standing on that matter. I just want you to know that you handled an impossible situation in a very admirable and loving manner. You never once raised your voice or reflected ugliness back at her. It made me admire you more as a person instead of just what I love about the amazing career you paved for yourself. My hope is that people really look into this instead of just clinging to the gossip and ugliness that so many people seem to be drawn to these days. As a survivor of abuse myself I think there needs to be attention brought to the many people who stand behind such allegations of abuse for sympathy, fame and/or simply just to get a leg up in a legal battle. It cheapens what so many true victims have been through. In my opinion it is also a form of abuse against whom ever they make false allegations against. It’s despicable. I also think you were a fantastic example (on the recording I heard) of how to attempt to de- escalate a volatile situation and maintain  a respectful conversation. So many people would love to have a partner who listened and communicated like you did in that recording. 

We do get angry. It is in our nature as humans. However, just because you’re angry does not mean that you cannot be angry and maintain respect for your loved one. (I heard you say the same thing to her almost verbatim.) Anytime there is violence you should walk away and leave the situation for however long it takes to de-escalate and bring each party back to a level of enough calm to have an intelligent, meaningful conversation. You did the right thing Mr. Depp. That is not a cowardly action. That is the action of someone who is level headed enough to do what needs to be done to protect BOTH individuals involved. I commend you for that. Unfortunately, we can’t rationalize with the irrational. No one can say you didn’t try. 

There are lessons to be learned for everyone who sees this mess she created. I just hope people try to see what those lessons are. 

Best wishes and ❤️ much love❤️
